The 2009 CrossFit Games were held on July 10-12, 2009 on a ranch in Aromas, California. The men's competition, with a field of 74 competitors, was won by Mikko Salo. The women's, with a field of 72, was won by Tanya Wagner. The team competition by Northwest CrossFit. This was the first Games to include separate team based events, regional qualifiers for individual competitors, and steroid testing.
